President Donald J. Trump intends to nominate Michael Griffin of Alabama to be the Under Secretary of Defense for Research and Engineering, effective February 1, 2018. Griffin previously served as the Chairman and CEO of the Schafer Corporation and as the Administrator of NASA. He has received several prestigious awards for his work in the field of space exploration. In addition, President Trump intends to appoint several individuals to the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations for four-year terms.